WEBVTT

00:50.049 --> 00:51.134
ALL FIGURES,
INCIDENTS, LOCATIONS,

00:51.217 --> 00:52.469
ORGANIZATIONS,
AND OTHERS ARE FICTITIOUS.

00:52.552 --> 00:53.970
CHILD ACTORS AND ANIMALS
WERE FILMED SAFELY

00:54.054 --> 00:54.971
IN ACCORDANCE WITH GUIDELINES.

01:01.895 --> 01:06.316
SHIN I-RANG, HAN NA-HYUN
LAW OFFICE

01:16.117 --> 01:18.453
How may I help you?

01:20.038 --> 01:21.164
Ma'am!

01:26.127 --> 01:29.339
So that's why I didn't see you lately.

01:30.840 --> 01:32.258
Did you pass away?

01:35.011 --> 01:37.806
You struggled so much,
only to pass away like this.

01:39.474 --> 01:41.226
-Ouch!
-What are you saying?

01:41.810 --> 01:44.145
I'm not dead yet.

01:44.229 --> 01:45.230
Oh.

01:46.856 --> 01:49.526
-Geez.
-You really aren't dead!

01:50.860 --> 01:52.153
Thank you.

01:52.237 --> 01:53.571
Thank you so much.

01:53.655 --> 01:56.658
You silly young man.

01:56.741 --> 01:57.742
Unbelievable.

01:57.826 --> 01:59.828
You came early.
I bought some coffee for you.

02:01.204 --> 02:02.664
Hello.

02:02.747 --> 02:03.915
Oh, dear.

02:06.084 --> 02:07.293
I can see her too.

02:07.377 --> 02:08.920
Attorney Han, this is…

02:14.175 --> 02:16.052
I can even touch her.

02:17.220 --> 02:19.681
Of course, you can. She's not a ghost.

02:21.182 --> 02:22.183
She's not?

02:22.267 --> 02:25.145
Why are you both so eager to call me dead?

02:25.228 --> 02:27.522
-I'm sorry.
-Sorry about that.

02:28.690 --> 02:30.859
Ma'am, why don't we sit down and talk?

02:30.942 --> 02:32.068
Sure.

02:39.868 --> 02:40.910
Who is she?

02:41.452 --> 02:43.913
She's a close acquaintance of mine.

02:46.291 --> 02:48.793
What brings you here?

02:48.877 --> 02:51.713
I'm here to meet you, young attorney.

02:51.796 --> 02:52.797
Why?

02:52.881 --> 02:54.799
Did you get caught up in any trouble?

02:56.801 --> 02:58.386
No, nothing like that.

02:59.262 --> 03:01.472
It's because of my late husband.

03:11.149 --> 03:15.612
Does he perhaps have
silver hair, bushy eyebrows…

03:18.031 --> 03:19.115
and a handsome face?

03:19.198 --> 03:20.325
Oh, my.

03:21.284 --> 03:24.078
Words say the attorney here is
nearly psychic.

03:24.162 --> 03:25.705
It must be true.

03:26.289 --> 03:28.333
An attorney doesn't need psychic powers.

03:28.416 --> 03:30.668
Oh, my head!

03:33.630 --> 03:37.383
Did your husband have
some kind of disease?

03:37.967 --> 03:38.968
Well,

03:39.802 --> 03:41.012
he had Alzheimer's.

03:43.139 --> 03:46.392
He came back to his senses
from time to time,

03:47.143 --> 03:50.438
but most of the time,
he only had memories of his earlier years.

03:50.521 --> 03:52.148
It must've been hard.

04:02.200 --> 04:06.955
Did he perhaps have something
to do with shoes?

04:07.038 --> 04:09.540
How did you know?

04:09.624 --> 04:12.126
He was a shoemaker.

04:14.629 --> 04:16.965
Even when we met the first time,

04:18.174 --> 04:20.134
he was making shoes.

04:21.761 --> 04:23.137
YEAR 1979

04:24.973 --> 04:27.684
He was awfully rude to me.

04:27.767 --> 04:30.186
-<i>At the time…</i>
-So I…

04:30.270 --> 04:33.815
<i>…Seoul was a magical city</i>
<i>where everything changed overnight.</i>

04:33.898 --> 04:37.568
<i>I was a young girl with splendid dreams.</i>

04:37.652 --> 04:39.696
Still, he's a premed student
at Hanguk University.

04:39.779 --> 04:41.864
Isn't he great husband material?

04:42.448 --> 04:44.325
So what if he's great husband material?

04:44.409 --> 04:46.119
I'm the one who's going to be the best.

04:47.287 --> 04:48.871
That sounds so like you.

04:50.581 --> 04:52.500
Even so, it's a shame.

04:52.583 --> 04:55.670
There isn't anyone suited to be
your husband as much as he is.

04:57.839 --> 04:59.299
What are you doing?

05:00.675 --> 05:02.135
I'm leaving without you.

05:03.344 --> 05:04.929
He's so cool.

05:23.197 --> 05:24.282
Are you here for new shoes?

05:24.907 --> 05:25.908
Excuse me?

05:26.492 --> 05:28.870
The showroom is over there.
This is the workshop.

05:28.953 --> 05:30.288
I know that.

05:30.955 --> 05:33.416
And what I need isn't new shoes…

05:37.462 --> 05:38.880
but you.

05:40.590 --> 05:44.844
<i>Back then, I was preparing</i>
<i>to open my own shop</i>

05:44.927 --> 05:47.472
<i>with the marriage fund</i>
<i>I got from my parents</i>

05:47.555 --> 05:50.308
<i>after graduating</i>
<i>from a famous fashion academy.</i>

05:50.391 --> 05:53.478
Shoes that make you happy
as soon as you wear them.

05:54.145 --> 05:57.065
Shoes that feel like
they will take you somewhere nice.

05:58.399 --> 06:01.694
To make the finest shoes
made with sincerity.

06:01.778 --> 06:03.112
That was my dream.

06:03.654 --> 06:05.615
MERRY SHOES

06:07.658 --> 06:11.204
The best kind of shoes aren't made
simply with money and skills.

06:11.871 --> 06:14.957
Without fine leather,
the best kind of shoes cannot exist.

06:15.041 --> 06:17.585
I also know
that quality leather is a must.

06:18.544 --> 06:20.213
Which company's leather do you want?

06:21.130 --> 06:22.256
Is it imported leather?

06:23.633 --> 06:25.718
From Italy? France?

06:30.765 --> 06:32.391
There's someone I want you to meet.

06:37.063 --> 06:38.898
<i>Seon Hwa was from Hamgyong, North Korea.</i>

06:38.981 --> 06:41.234
-Seon Hwa.
-<i>She burnished the leather alone</i>

06:41.317 --> 06:43.986
<i>without anyone's help.</i>

06:44.070 --> 06:47.907
<i>Her leather was soft like a feather,</i>
<i>yet strong like metal.</i>

06:47.990 --> 06:50.701
<i>I fell in love with it straightaway.</i>

06:50.785 --> 06:51.994
IDEAL SHOES

06:52.078 --> 06:53.412
Don't be nervous.

06:54.288 --> 06:55.748
Everyone, relax.

06:55.832 --> 06:57.834
One, two, three.

07:00.419 --> 07:02.547
-One more time.
-<i>That was how</i>

07:02.630 --> 07:05.341
-<i>we opened Ideal Shoes.</i>
-One, two, three.

07:06.259 --> 07:08.970
Ideal Shoes? Do you mean <i>that</i> Ideal Shoes?

07:09.053 --> 07:11.305
Yes, that's the one.

07:12.098 --> 07:13.182
Seriously?

07:13.266 --> 07:15.977
My heels right now are Ideal Shoes.

07:17.395 --> 07:18.646
Oh, that.

07:18.729 --> 07:22.733
It's from our steady-selling line
that's been produced since 1981.

07:24.110 --> 07:25.653
You have an eye for shoes.

07:26.904 --> 07:27.905
Wow.

07:28.573 --> 07:30.616
I see you in a whole new light.

07:32.243 --> 07:35.663
But why did you quit working?

07:35.746 --> 07:37.248
You're still healthy and well.

07:38.040 --> 07:42.211
I had to focus on something
more important than work.

07:43.796 --> 07:45.173
Anyway,

07:45.882 --> 07:50.386
the three of us opened this shop alone
with a small budget,

07:50.470 --> 07:53.681
but we were confident
in the products we made.

08:40.770 --> 08:44.148
-They're so pretty.
-<i>That's how our shoes</i>

08:44.232 --> 08:46.609
<i>started to fill the display cabinets.</i>

08:47.944 --> 08:51.781
<i>More and more people loved our products.</i>

08:51.864 --> 08:53.199
One, two, three.

08:54.116 --> 08:57.537
-Smile a little more.
-<i>We'd make shoes all night,</i>

08:57.620 --> 08:59.789
<i>but we couldn't stop smiling.</i>

08:59.872 --> 09:00.873
IDEAL SHOES

09:00.957 --> 09:02.124
Get in closer.

09:02.208 --> 09:03.918
One, two, three.

09:08.839 --> 09:11.217
<i>It was when I learned</i>

09:11.300 --> 09:16.264
<i>that Seon Hwa left behind</i>
<i>her newborn baby in North Korea.</i>

09:16.806 --> 09:17.807
What are you doing?

09:19.183 --> 09:20.726
I was making a wish.

09:21.352 --> 09:25.022
To meet my son in North Korea again.

09:28.651 --> 09:29.652
Oh.

09:30.903 --> 09:32.280
I'll also make a prayer

09:32.863 --> 09:34.615
for your wish to come true.

09:36.117 --> 09:37.118
Me too.

09:39.787 --> 09:43.541
<i>We felt like we had the world.</i>

09:44.250 --> 09:45.751
<i>We had nothing to fear.</i>

09:55.219 --> 09:56.220
<i>Not until</i>

09:57.388 --> 09:59.181
<i>Seon Hwa got arrested.</i>

10:01.684 --> 10:03.477
She was accused of being a spy.

10:04.854 --> 10:05.855
It turned out

10:07.315 --> 10:09.483
Seon Hwa was sending money to North Korea.

10:12.278 --> 10:13.279
Let me go!

10:13.904 --> 10:17.658
<i>She explained that the money was</i>
<i>for her family in the North.</i>

10:17.742 --> 10:20.494
-Wait. Let go!
-She's innocent.

10:20.578 --> 10:22.788
-She isn't a spy.
-Seon Hwa!

10:22.872 --> 10:24.040
<i>However,</i>

10:25.041 --> 10:27.084
<i>what we got in return</i>
<i>was a frightening threat.</i>

10:28.628 --> 10:30.838
<i>They questioned if we were also involved.</i>

10:31.505 --> 10:34.467
<i>If so, Ideal Shoes was</i>
<i>to close down right away.</i>

10:36.385 --> 10:39.347
My husband and I couldn't say a thing.

10:40.848 --> 10:43.142
If the company closed down,

10:44.101 --> 10:47.605
dozens of employees were to go jobless.

10:48.272 --> 10:50.816
And their families added up to hundreds.

10:53.444 --> 10:54.445
In the end,

10:55.071 --> 10:59.367
we could do nothing
but hope that she'd be released safely.

11:01.285 --> 11:03.746
The years went by.

11:04.455 --> 11:06.624
When we went to visit her,

11:08.042 --> 11:09.418
she was

11:09.502 --> 11:11.545
already dead.

11:13.839 --> 11:18.219
<i>We made her grave on a hill</i>
<i>where North Korea was visible</i>

11:19.178 --> 11:21.639
<i>and buried her cremation urn there.</i>

11:22.890 --> 11:24.558
<i>It was devastating.</i>

11:26.644 --> 11:30.523
<i>Only if we had visited her sooner…</i>

11:31.232 --> 11:35.694
<i>Only if we hadn't cared about the company</i>
<i>and saved her…</i>

11:37.405 --> 11:40.741
<i>Then, she may still be alive.</i>

11:42.618 --> 11:46.997
Struggling with regret,
we made up our minds

11:48.499 --> 11:51.377
<i>to find her son in North Korea</i>

11:51.460 --> 11:52.962
<i>and give her share to him.</i>

11:53.045 --> 11:54.713
Please make sure to find him.

11:55.798 --> 11:56.799
I'm sorry.

11:57.550 --> 12:00.344
I see. Thank you
for your hard work, though.

12:00.428 --> 12:01.429
I'm sorry.

12:01.512 --> 12:03.764
I see. Thank you.

12:04.473 --> 12:05.558
We appreciate it.

12:06.225 --> 12:10.271
<i>But it wasn't easy to find her son.</i>

12:10.354 --> 12:11.439
WILL

12:11.522 --> 12:13.357
<i>My husband ended up</i>

12:14.233 --> 12:18.696
<i>writing a will about leaving him</i>
<i>an inheritance out of anxiety.</i>

12:20.156 --> 12:24.118
And after a year since he passed away,

12:24.827 --> 12:26.078
her son,

12:26.162 --> 12:29.707
Cha Eun Seong, was found at last.

12:30.916 --> 12:33.210
It says the heir must provide

12:33.294 --> 12:35.880
one-third of the inheritance
to Ms. Ryeo Seon Hwa's son,

12:35.963 --> 12:38.507
Cha Eun Seong, if he is found at any time.

12:38.591 --> 12:40.926
Most of the inheritance is
the shares of Ideal Shoes.

12:41.427 --> 12:44.680
The company will be at stake
if one-third of it is given to him.

12:45.931 --> 12:50.227
Ms. Ryeo Seon Hwa's contributions
to Ideal Shoes are mentioned as a reason.

12:51.604 --> 12:55.483
The case will be in our favor
if your mother is against this will.

12:55.566 --> 12:56.650
What's her opinion?

12:57.318 --> 13:00.404
My mother thinks it's only right
to do as my father's will says.

13:01.113 --> 13:04.742
She told Cha Eun Seong
about my father's will herself.

13:06.452 --> 13:07.870
She's always been like this.

13:07.953 --> 13:10.539
She can't stand to enjoy any luxuries

13:12.166 --> 13:14.084
when Ms. Ryeo wrongfully
passed away in prison.

13:14.168 --> 13:17.755
-Thank you. Have a great day.
-Thank you. Enjoy.

13:18.297 --> 13:20.382
<i>She lives alone in an old, small house.</i>

13:21.091 --> 13:24.094
<i>She sells vegetables on the street</i>
<i>no matter how hard I try to stop her.</i>

13:24.178 --> 13:25.304
Welcome.

13:26.347 --> 13:28.432
Normally, she lets me
have my way with everything.

13:28.933 --> 13:31.602
But she thundered at me
when I refused to give the money.

13:32.186 --> 13:35.564
She said she'd even take it to court
if she needed to.

13:37.650 --> 13:38.651
I see.

13:39.527 --> 13:41.070
All right for now.

13:41.153 --> 13:43.405
We'll have to check more in detail,

13:43.489 --> 13:45.282
but the deceased's will exists

13:45.366 --> 13:48.410
along with your mother's strong intention
to execute it.

13:48.494 --> 13:50.079
Thus, a trial seems inevitable.

13:50.162 --> 13:53.082
Then, we must win this case.

14:00.631 --> 14:03.342
Why don't you try persuading your son?

14:04.009 --> 14:07.972
You'll have to go to trial
against your son at this rate.

14:08.889 --> 14:10.516
It'll be tough.

14:10.599 --> 14:13.185
I've already tried.

14:13.769 --> 14:15.271
He's adamant.

14:15.854 --> 14:17.064
That's understandable.

14:17.731 --> 14:21.819
I honestly doubt your son could accept it.

14:22.319 --> 14:25.155
Not unless you compromised
with a much lower amount.

14:25.239 --> 14:27.199
I won't compromise.

14:27.283 --> 14:29.285
I'll never settle for a lower amount.

14:29.994 --> 14:32.413
Even if it's taken to court,

14:32.997 --> 14:35.040
I want to follow my husband's will.

14:35.749 --> 14:37.084
But…

14:37.167 --> 14:38.419
Okay.

14:38.502 --> 14:40.588
We understand, ma'am.

14:41.171 --> 14:43.257
Please go home for today.

14:43.340 --> 14:46.635
We'll get back to you
after a thorough check.

14:47.761 --> 14:48.762
Oh…

14:50.681 --> 14:51.765
Here.

14:53.267 --> 14:56.562
You can find materials and pictures
about Seon Hwa in this envelope.

14:56.645 --> 14:59.899
My number is in it too.

15:00.524 --> 15:04.570
Please help me keep my husband's promise.

15:07.615 --> 15:08.699
We'll see what can be done.

15:10.910 --> 15:11.994
Oh, right.

15:12.077 --> 15:14.330
We need to know about your husband

15:14.413 --> 15:16.874
if we're to prepare for the trial.

15:17.499 --> 15:20.127
May I know his name and date of birth?

15:20.210 --> 15:22.087
His name is

15:22.630 --> 15:24.006
Kang Dong-sik.

15:25.049 --> 15:29.845
He was born on March 1, 1953.

15:31.722 --> 15:33.223
I'll be counting on you.

15:44.985 --> 15:46.654
WILL

16:10.386 --> 16:11.929
Hello, sir.

16:12.012 --> 16:13.013
How do you do?

16:13.097 --> 16:17.142
I'm Kang Dong-sik, the shoemaker.

16:17.226 --> 16:19.061
I'm Attorney Shin I-rang.

16:19.144 --> 16:21.230
This is Attorney Han Na-hyun.

16:23.065 --> 16:25.442
Hello, I'm Attorney Han Na-hyun.

16:25.526 --> 16:27.820
I'm right here.

16:29.655 --> 16:32.533
-Oh, right. You can't see me.
-He's over there.

16:33.367 --> 16:34.952
It's nice to meet you.

16:35.035 --> 16:36.537
He says it's nice to meet you.

16:37.287 --> 16:39.790
Anyway, I see

16:39.873 --> 16:42.126
you're easygoing

16:42.209 --> 16:46.130
and practical, yet polished.

16:47.256 --> 16:50.509
And you mostly sit
with your left leg crossed.

16:51.385 --> 16:53.512
How did you know?

16:54.388 --> 16:57.349
One's shoes tell everything about them.

16:58.684 --> 17:02.896
You've worn those uncomfortable shoes
until the heels are frayed.

17:02.980 --> 17:05.315
It means you have
an easygoing personality.

17:05.983 --> 17:07.860
Those are machine-stitched shoes

17:07.943 --> 17:10.112
made with synthetic leather,

17:10.195 --> 17:13.323
but you chose a classic design.

17:13.991 --> 17:16.535
It means your taste isn't half bad.

17:16.618 --> 17:17.953
Gosh.

17:18.037 --> 17:22.791
The right heel is frayed
more than the left heel

17:22.875 --> 17:25.794
because your pelvis is misaligned
from crossing your legs.

17:26.295 --> 17:29.715
But it's not too serious, so don't worry.

17:30.382 --> 17:32.676
Wow, amazing.

17:34.636 --> 17:36.013
What is it? What did he say?

17:37.097 --> 17:40.392
He got it all right about me
just by looking at my shoes.

17:42.561 --> 17:45.564
What about the old lady from earlier?

17:46.565 --> 17:48.067
I could sense

17:48.609 --> 17:52.946
a diligent and humble nature
from her shoes.

17:55.491 --> 17:58.118
He doesn't recognize Ms. Chae.

17:59.536 --> 18:02.414
Can you hand me one of the pictures
we got from her?

18:03.248 --> 18:05.250
What if he possesses you?

18:05.834 --> 18:08.337
We need to do anything
to help him regain his memory.

18:09.505 --> 18:13.300
And he doesn't seem dangerous.
It might be okay even if he possesses me.

18:24.895 --> 18:27.564
IDEAL SHOES

18:38.951 --> 18:39.952
Oh, boy.

18:40.702 --> 18:41.745
I'm running late.

18:44.123 --> 18:47.751
Where's the young man that was just here?

18:49.294 --> 18:51.964
Excuse me for asking, miss stranger,

18:52.589 --> 18:55.175
but where is the nearest bus stop?

18:55.759 --> 18:57.177
Why do you ask?

18:57.261 --> 18:59.847
I need to go to Malli-dong to make shoes.

19:00.639 --> 19:04.351
Customers will be disappointed
if I don't have the shoes ready on time.

19:04.434 --> 19:05.602
This is bad.

19:07.271 --> 19:08.397
Sir.

19:09.356 --> 19:11.525
Malli-dong isn't the same anymore.

19:12.109 --> 19:14.862
What? What do you mean by that?

19:17.030 --> 19:18.574
What I mean is--

19:18.657 --> 19:19.700
Miss.

19:19.783 --> 19:21.660
I'm really sorry,

19:21.743 --> 19:24.246
but I don't have time to hear you out.

19:25.747 --> 19:27.791
To my customers,

19:28.584 --> 19:30.252
my products mean more than just shoes.

19:30.878 --> 19:33.297
They're partners for success

19:33.380 --> 19:35.716
and life companions for their new lives.

19:38.218 --> 19:41.471
Oh, I'm running out of time.

19:41.555 --> 19:44.016
I have business there anyway.

19:44.099 --> 19:45.100
Let me accompany you.

19:45.184 --> 19:47.728
Sure, please lead the way.

19:53.108 --> 19:58.238
OKCHEON BUILDING

20:08.248 --> 20:10.500
Sir, please wait inside for a second.

20:10.584 --> 20:11.835
Okay.

20:47.704 --> 20:48.956
My goodness.

20:58.757 --> 21:00.300
-Excuse me, ma'am.
-Yes?

21:00.384 --> 21:03.053
-May I ask you something?
-Okay?

21:03.637 --> 21:07.307
What bus should I take
to get to Malli-dong?

21:07.391 --> 21:11.186
Bus number 0411
will take you straight there.

21:12.938 --> 21:14.273
Here it comes.

21:19.569 --> 21:20.988
Why, thank you.

21:21.071 --> 21:22.072
Sure.

21:28.161 --> 21:29.371
Wait!

21:47.681 --> 21:50.642
BUS 0411

21:52.936 --> 21:54.563
MALLI-DONG HANDMADE SHOE STREET

21:57.607 --> 22:00.152
Sir, please take me
to the handmade shoe street in Malli-dong.

22:00.235 --> 22:01.236
Okay.

22:13.623 --> 22:15.709
This must be the place.

22:18.128 --> 22:19.713
Welcome.

22:29.806 --> 22:32.225
How strange.

22:34.269 --> 22:36.146
This has to be the place.

22:36.813 --> 22:38.148
Excuse me.

22:38.815 --> 22:40.400
What are you looking for?

22:44.321 --> 22:45.822
Do you need anything?

22:45.906 --> 22:49.284
This is supposed to be my workshop.

22:49.367 --> 22:51.286
What's all this flashy stuff?

22:51.369 --> 22:52.662
Who are you, mister?

22:52.746 --> 22:55.373
I'm a shoemaker.

22:55.957 --> 22:57.959
-Where are my shoes?
-Get out.

22:58.043 --> 23:00.253
This place is my workshop.

23:00.337 --> 23:03.173
-There's no workshop here. Get out.
-What's the matter with you?

23:07.219 --> 23:08.887
This has to be it.

24:00.230 --> 24:01.648
Attorney Shin!

25:36.993 --> 25:39.246
Here, try it on.

25:46.211 --> 25:47.295
I'm sorry.

25:48.505 --> 25:50.715
I thought he'd remember something

25:51.216 --> 25:53.551
if I took him out
and let him see things for himself.

25:55.011 --> 25:56.638
I shouldn't have.

25:59.557 --> 26:00.558
Excuse me,

26:01.977 --> 26:03.895
but do you know me?

26:26.668 --> 26:29.129
You must've been so lonely alone.

26:33.800 --> 26:35.635
I'll help you from now on.

26:59.117 --> 27:02.704
SHIN I-RANG LAW OFFICE

27:07.667 --> 27:09.461
What are you going to do with this case?

27:09.544 --> 27:12.672
I think we should settle at a fair level.

27:13.673 --> 27:14.841
You think so?

27:17.010 --> 27:21.931
I believe my duty as her attorney is
to help her execute her husband's will.

27:24.559 --> 27:25.810
It's not likely, is it?

27:30.648 --> 27:32.484
Nevertheless, you'll fight to the end.

27:36.988 --> 27:38.198
I get it now.

27:38.990 --> 27:40.700
I'll have to work my butt off.

27:41.284 --> 27:43.036
Are you going to help me?

27:43.119 --> 27:46.164
We share this office,
and you're up against Taebaek.

27:46.956 --> 27:49.084
It would be heartless
to let you fight alone.

27:49.626 --> 27:52.212
Instead, we'll split
the contingency fee fifty-fifty.

27:57.258 --> 27:58.385
Deal.

28:12.982 --> 28:16.528
Father, did you give the Ideal Shoes case
to someone else?

28:16.611 --> 28:17.946
I did.

28:18.530 --> 28:21.324
Why? I even consulted
with CEO Kang Ji-hoon myself.

28:21.408 --> 28:23.910
Shin I-rang and Han Na-hyun
are defending the other side.

28:25.620 --> 28:26.621
So what?

28:30.166 --> 28:32.502
Personal feelings may hinder
an attorney's judgment.

28:32.585 --> 28:34.796
So, I had someone else take charge of it.

28:34.879 --> 28:37.966
No, I have no personal feelings.

28:39.384 --> 28:40.385
Let me do it.

28:41.094 --> 28:43.805
I'll prove myself, Father.

29:00.238 --> 29:01.489
You're saying

29:01.573 --> 29:03.783
this is where I used to live?

29:06.035 --> 29:08.037
I don't remember,

29:09.581 --> 29:11.833
but it feels very familiar.

29:14.836 --> 29:16.421
WORKROOM

29:43.656 --> 29:45.074
This is…

29:45.158 --> 29:46.618
What was it…

29:50.580 --> 29:52.999
What is it? Do you remember anything?

29:54.000 --> 29:56.836
What was this again?

29:58.838 --> 30:00.256
So, these…

30:05.887 --> 30:08.264
used to belong to my husband.

30:08.348 --> 30:10.350
I couldn't throw them out.

30:14.562 --> 30:16.397
It's a relief we have a lot to refer to.

30:16.481 --> 30:17.941
Thank goodness.

30:20.235 --> 30:22.237
Look at this old thing.

30:32.080 --> 30:34.958
Oh, my goodness.
I-rang, what are you doing?

30:35.041 --> 30:37.961
Don't wear this kind of thing!

30:38.545 --> 30:39.546
Sir.

30:39.629 --> 30:42.757
His shoes are for easy wear.

30:42.841 --> 30:45.051
So what if they're easy to wear?

30:45.134 --> 30:46.970
They're classless!

30:47.720 --> 30:48.847
Bah!

30:49.764 --> 30:51.933
-Hmph.
-I-rang!

30:52.016 --> 30:53.977
Seriously? This is the fifth floor!

30:54.060 --> 30:55.311
Geez!

30:57.063 --> 31:00.108
Let me start the briefing
about Kang Ji-hoon's will contest.

31:01.776 --> 31:03.987
"Will. I, Kang Dong-sik,
leave this as my last will."

31:04.070 --> 31:07.282
We must focus on this date.

31:07.365 --> 31:08.616
That needs to be checked.

31:08.700 --> 31:10.159
I'm putting Attorney Oh on it.

31:10.243 --> 31:11.870
Excuse me. Let me ask you something.

31:11.953 --> 31:13.162
-Yes?
-Well…

31:14.205 --> 31:16.040
Do you know these people?

31:16.124 --> 31:17.333
IDEAL SHOES

31:17.959 --> 31:19.252
No, I don't.

31:20.628 --> 31:22.922
I see. Thank you.

31:35.727 --> 31:36.811
Hello.

31:42.442 --> 31:44.903
Do you perhaps know these people?

32:05.298 --> 32:06.299
Let's go.

32:16.809 --> 32:18.061
2010 COMMERCIAL
2015 COMMERCIAL

32:21.773 --> 32:23.066
WHY OLD KOREANS LEAVE A WILL

32:23.858 --> 32:25.193
TESTIMONY
KANG JI-HOON, IDEAL SHOES CEO

32:25.276 --> 32:28.863
Now that we've visited the field
and collected enough materials,

32:29.739 --> 32:32.533
why don't we go meet Mr. Cha Eun Seong,
Ms. Ryeo Seon Hwa's son?

32:33.451 --> 32:34.494
Give it to me!

32:35.161 --> 32:36.913
I said no to these shoes!

32:37.413 --> 32:39.832
-Take the other one off immediately!
-Attorney Han, stop him!

32:39.916 --> 32:40.917
Bah!

32:44.671 --> 32:46.005
Thanks, Attorney Han!

32:54.389 --> 32:56.265
Wow.

32:56.349 --> 32:58.935
It's leather.

33:03.523 --> 33:06.192
-Excuse me. May I ask you something?
-Yes?

33:06.776 --> 33:08.820
I'm looking for Mr. Cha Eun Seong.

33:08.903 --> 33:10.905
Our chief? He's over there.

33:11.614 --> 33:12.740
Chief.

33:21.708 --> 33:23.793
You're having a late lunch today.

33:23.876 --> 33:25.503
It's not good to skip meals.

33:25.586 --> 33:27.755
Come by anytime.

33:27.839 --> 33:29.007
Okay?

33:29.590 --> 33:31.426
And eat up.

33:31.509 --> 33:33.094
I will, ma'am.

33:33.678 --> 33:35.388
-Enjoy.
-Thank you.

33:37.432 --> 33:38.891
I eat here every day.

33:39.600 --> 33:40.810
Are you okay with noodles?

33:40.893 --> 33:43.104
I can handle anything.

33:48.484 --> 33:49.819
This is delicious.

33:49.902 --> 33:50.903
It's good.

33:58.453 --> 33:59.787
I'm all right.

34:00.413 --> 34:01.831
Feel free to ask me questions.

34:02.457 --> 34:05.543
When did you come to Korea?

34:06.169 --> 34:07.754
I hear your hometown is in North Korea.

34:08.421 --> 34:09.422
That's right.

34:10.298 --> 34:13.843
I was born in Hamgyong and separated
from my mother when I was one.

34:13.926 --> 34:17.013
After my aunt died,
I came to Korea more than ten years ago.

34:17.597 --> 34:21.059
How did you come
to dye leather for a living?

34:22.143 --> 34:24.145
My hometown is known for leather-dyeing.

34:24.228 --> 34:26.189
All my family and relatives
were in the field.

34:28.900 --> 34:31.778
When I heard my mother was
in the same line of work,

34:33.154 --> 34:34.572
it broke my heart.

34:35.948 --> 34:39.619
How much do you know about your mother?

34:40.203 --> 34:43.706
I heard she kept sending money
to my family in the North

34:43.790 --> 34:46.417
and tried to get us out of the country.

34:46.501 --> 34:50.004
And that she lost contact with us
as soon as we arrived in China.

34:54.133 --> 34:55.676
<i>Moving on to the next story.</i>

34:56.260 --> 34:59.388
<i>"Today is the first death anniversary</i>

34:59.472 --> 35:01.599
<i>of my beloved wife."</i>

35:02.391 --> 35:05.728
<i>"I've been trying</i>
<i>to keep a level head for my children,</i>

35:05.812 --> 35:07.855
<i>but it's not so easy."</i>

35:08.815 --> 35:11.818
<i>"Whenever I listen to the songs she liked,</i>

35:11.901 --> 35:14.320
<i>pass by the road we often walked together,</i>

35:15.154 --> 35:17.448
<i>or look at the food we enjoyed together,</i>

35:18.032 --> 35:19.450
<i>I'm reminded of my wife."</i>

35:20.201 --> 35:22.078
<i>"I miss her so much"--</i>

35:24.038 --> 35:26.707
He doesn't even know
that his mother passed away.

35:27.291 --> 35:28.584
I feel so bad for him.

35:30.336 --> 35:32.505
I guess Ms. Chae
couldn't possibly inform him

35:33.089 --> 35:35.007
of his mother's death.

35:35.591 --> 35:38.594
We'd better tell him eventually
when we get a chance.

35:51.190 --> 35:54.193
PITTER-PATTER BUTCHER-STYLE BBQ

35:55.570 --> 35:57.947
Go in without me.
I'll park the truck and follow you.

35:58.030 --> 35:59.115
Wait.

36:04.162 --> 36:05.413
What is this?

36:13.337 --> 36:14.839
SHIN I-RANG

36:15.965 --> 36:18.384
Isn't this your phone number?

36:19.218 --> 36:20.678
In case you go missing again.

36:22.972 --> 36:25.850
-Attorney Han.
-To make it easier to look for you.

36:27.393 --> 36:28.811
Park and come up.

36:31.397 --> 36:35.943
OKCHEON BUILDING

36:43.701 --> 36:45.536
Oh, it must be love.

36:47.997 --> 36:50.208
It's nothing like that.

36:50.291 --> 36:52.668
Ghosts can see everything.

37:11.979 --> 37:13.231
That's right.

37:15.942 --> 37:18.653
<i>This is love</i>

37:55.564 --> 37:57.858
<i>What should I do?</i>

37:58.359 --> 38:01.946
<i>If you suddenly leave me behind</i>

38:36.981 --> 38:39.233
WORKROOM

39:36.040 --> 39:38.000
Even so, it's a shame.

39:38.084 --> 39:41.003
There isn't anyone suited to be
your husband as much as he is.

39:45.508 --> 39:46.967
He's so cool.

39:50.638 --> 39:52.848
DEAR DONG-SIK
…I CAN'T HIDE MY FEELINGS ANYMORE…

40:07.571 --> 40:11.325
DAEUN CHOCOLATE

41:17.975 --> 41:19.560
CONGRATS ON
HAN NA-HYUN'S GRAND OPENING

41:21.312 --> 41:22.730
What am I doing here?

41:25.733 --> 41:27.151
Snap out of it.

41:32.156 --> 41:34.158
SEOUL
VACANT

41:35.784 --> 41:38.746
Hi, Na-hyun. Are you still at the office?

41:39.246 --> 41:43.250
Your mom sent me to deliver a lunch box
for you and Attorney Shin.

41:43.792 --> 41:46.253
But I don't see any space to park.

41:46.795 --> 41:48.422
Okay, take your time coming downstairs.

41:48.506 --> 41:49.798
See you soon.

41:49.882 --> 41:51.258
Oops.

41:55.804 --> 41:56.805
Oh, my.

42:05.272 --> 42:06.398
What was that?

42:06.482 --> 42:07.608
Oh, no. I-I'm sorry.

42:07.691 --> 42:09.193
Were you even looking at the road?

42:09.276 --> 42:11.320
I'm so sorry, sir.

42:11.403 --> 42:12.571
Unbelievable.

42:13.572 --> 42:16.283
Repairing the bumper alone
would cost as much as your cab.

42:16.909 --> 42:17.910
I'm so sorry.

42:19.203 --> 42:20.204
Are you drunk?

42:20.788 --> 42:22.206
No, not at all.

42:22.289 --> 42:23.290
Dad?

42:23.832 --> 42:25.084
Oh, hey.

42:28.337 --> 42:29.380
My goodness.

42:29.964 --> 42:31.423
That's crumpled up bad.

42:31.507 --> 42:33.926
On second look, it's a minor scratch.

42:34.009 --> 42:35.344
-What?
-It's a scratch.

42:35.427 --> 42:36.762
No, I just crashed--

42:36.845 --> 42:38.305
It was already like this.

42:38.389 --> 42:40.808
It's all right. Are you not injured?

42:40.891 --> 42:42.810
I'm okay, but you--

42:42.893 --> 42:45.271
I'm okay because I'm young and strong.

42:45.354 --> 42:47.273
-Dad.
-Na-hyun.

42:48.274 --> 42:49.858
-Mr. Yang?
-Oh, hi.

42:50.442 --> 42:52.194
Do you know this man?

42:53.696 --> 42:57.199
You must be Attorney Han's father.

42:58.576 --> 43:02.371
Hello, I'm Managing Partner Yang Do-kyung
of her former workplace.

43:03.038 --> 43:05.958
Good lord, this is horrible.

43:06.750 --> 43:08.419
-Dear me.
-What's going on?

43:08.502 --> 43:11.714
Well, I was trying to stop
the lunch box from falling and…

43:11.797 --> 43:12.798
Oh.

43:13.507 --> 43:16.218
Sorry. We'll handle it through insurance.

43:16.302 --> 43:18.637
-Are you hurt?
-No, no. I'm not hurt.

43:18.721 --> 43:20.723
-I rammed into his car.
-Excuse me?

43:21.390 --> 43:23.601
No, I rammed into his car.

43:23.684 --> 43:26.061
What are you talking about?
I specialize in car accidents.

43:26.145 --> 43:28.105
I caused this accident, end of discussion.

43:28.689 --> 43:31.567
No, Na-hyun.
I really did ram into his car.

43:32.776 --> 43:34.361
What a complicated situation.

43:34.445 --> 43:36.363
I'll get going. I'll see you another time.

43:36.447 --> 43:37.448
Oh, okay.

43:37.990 --> 43:39.199
Mr. Yang.

43:39.283 --> 43:40.284
Yeah?

43:43.537 --> 43:45.748
-What is that?
-It's nothing.

43:45.831 --> 43:48.917
-Is it for me?
-No, it's for someone else.

43:49.543 --> 43:52.838
It says, "Congrats on
Han Na-hyun's grand opening."

43:56.884 --> 43:57.885
Oh, boy.

43:58.677 --> 43:59.887
Why is it written there?

44:01.263 --> 44:02.264
It's not for you.

44:17.905 --> 44:18.906
What the?

44:26.872 --> 44:29.208
What was I doing here?

44:31.210 --> 44:33.337
What did I do to make my hand like this?

44:36.882 --> 44:38.676
Where did my phone go?

44:40.803 --> 44:43.931
Sir, did something happen in your house?

44:44.515 --> 44:46.684
Yeah. I made shoes.

44:47.267 --> 44:48.644
-Shoes?
-Yes.

44:49.478 --> 44:50.479
Shoes for who?

44:53.524 --> 44:55.859
I can't remember.

45:10.416 --> 45:11.750
Why are you taking your shoes off?

45:12.960 --> 45:15.337
Oh, nothing. You're late.

45:16.088 --> 45:17.965
-Something came up.
-I see.

45:19.758 --> 45:21.385
Where did you get that plant?

45:22.428 --> 45:23.554
Guess what.

45:23.637 --> 45:26.348
Managing Partner Yang of Taebaek was here.

45:26.432 --> 45:28.183
-You mean, Yang Do-kyung?
-Yes.

45:29.518 --> 45:30.519
Where's Attorney Han?

45:30.602 --> 45:32.688
She stepped outside to see Mr. Yang off.

45:32.771 --> 45:34.523
Maybe they're having dinner together.

45:36.650 --> 45:38.068
Try calling her if you're curious.

45:38.152 --> 45:41.572
No, I don't think that's necessary.

45:45.951 --> 45:50.789
OKCHEON BUILDING

46:02.092 --> 46:03.093
SHIN I-RANG

46:04.470 --> 46:06.805
Takes a lot of work, doesn't it?

46:07.973 --> 46:10.309
I'm sorry. What did you just say?

46:11.018 --> 46:14.521
You've got to connect
two different individuals,

46:15.355 --> 46:17.024
smooth them out,

46:17.941 --> 46:21.195
and polish them from time to time,

46:21.278 --> 46:23.572
which is why it's so difficult.

46:24.865 --> 46:26.575
Both shoes

46:26.658 --> 46:28.118
and love.

46:30.329 --> 46:32.080
Love? What are you talking about?

46:32.164 --> 46:34.708
A ghost knows everything, brat.

46:37.002 --> 46:39.922
The two are also the same in a sense

46:40.005 --> 46:43.634
that they shine more
the more heart and soul you put into them.

46:45.135 --> 46:46.512
Oh, please.

46:53.727 --> 46:54.978
It's your brother-in-law.

46:55.521 --> 46:56.522
What?

46:58.065 --> 47:00.609
-I-rang.
-Bong-su?

47:07.866 --> 47:09.117
PITTER-PATTER BUTCHER-STYLE BBQ

47:09.201 --> 47:11.787
Attorney Han, what brings you here
at this hour--

47:11.870 --> 47:13.789
Where were you?
You said you'd park and come up.

47:14.498 --> 47:17.626
-Oh, I--
-Why didn't you answer your phone?

47:17.709 --> 47:19.253
I lost my phone--

47:19.336 --> 47:22.548
Also, why did you leave work
by yourself without waiting for me?

47:22.631 --> 47:24.174
You made me worry.

47:25.676 --> 47:28.887
I heard you left with Mr. Yang.

47:28.971 --> 47:30.973
-I didn't want to disturb.
-Disturb?

47:31.765 --> 47:35.227
There was a car accident. I handled it
through insurance and left him hours ago.

47:35.727 --> 47:37.521
I had no idea that you were home.

47:37.604 --> 47:39.856
I took this and looked everywhere
in Malli-dong for you!

47:41.942 --> 47:42.943
Really?

47:44.069 --> 47:46.530
Are you angry?

47:49.449 --> 47:50.993
I'm not angry…

47:51.868 --> 47:54.204
I'm just tired. My feet hurt too.

48:03.213 --> 48:04.214
Thanks.

48:06.383 --> 48:08.093
Thanks for what? I said I'm tired.

48:08.677 --> 48:10.762
How can you be this bad
at reading emotions?

48:13.932 --> 48:16.685
I'm sorry. I'll never do it again.

48:16.768 --> 48:18.103
Why are you laughing?

48:19.938 --> 48:20.939
I'm sorry.

48:21.023 --> 48:22.691
You say sorry at everything.

48:24.151 --> 48:25.777
What's wrong with you, really?

48:28.113 --> 48:30.741
Beats me. Why do I keep apologizing?

48:37.831 --> 48:39.333
Did you have dinner?

48:40.292 --> 48:41.376
You think I did?

48:41.918 --> 48:44.921
Me neither. Care to have dinner with me?

48:46.798 --> 48:47.966
What are we having?

48:48.550 --> 48:50.552
I know a delicious place nearby.

49:06.151 --> 49:08.737
-Welcome!
-Welcome!

49:16.161 --> 49:17.454
You must be hungry.

49:17.537 --> 49:19.539
Eat all you want, Attorney Han.

49:20.123 --> 49:21.333
This is unusual of you.

49:21.917 --> 49:22.918
Is today a special day?

49:23.001 --> 49:24.586
No,

49:24.670 --> 49:27.589
but you had a tough day because of me.

49:28.548 --> 49:29.716
You'll regret it.

49:30.300 --> 49:31.551
I'm a sushi killer.

49:34.012 --> 49:35.013
Me too.

49:38.767 --> 49:40.477
Where's the tuna?

49:41.103 --> 49:42.854
We can make an order.

49:42.938 --> 49:44.606
-Excuse me.
-Yes?

49:44.690 --> 49:46.692
Could you make us
two plates of tuna sushi?

49:46.775 --> 49:48.193
-Coming right away.
-Thank you.

49:49.403 --> 49:51.822
Wow, it looks good.

49:53.907 --> 49:56.326
-Here's your tuna.
-Thank you.

49:57.369 --> 49:58.370
Here you go.

50:08.046 --> 50:09.548
This is really good.

50:25.105 --> 50:26.189
I see you're loving it.

50:30.485 --> 50:31.570
It's delicious.

50:37.075 --> 50:38.618
Where did my shoes go?

50:38.702 --> 50:41.830
Mom, my Heartsping shoes are missing too.

50:41.913 --> 50:45.000
-That's odd.
-I was going to wear them.

50:45.709 --> 50:47.085
Sir.

50:47.169 --> 50:50.922
Take a slow look at these as you wait.

50:52.257 --> 50:54.468
You brought your whole family's shoes.

50:55.177 --> 50:56.178
Oh, dear.

50:57.637 --> 50:59.181
-See you later.
-Okay.

51:00.223 --> 51:01.600
PITTER-PATTER BUTCHER-STYLE BBQ

51:03.268 --> 51:04.603
Goodness, gracious.

51:05.896 --> 51:07.647
How are your feet?

51:09.024 --> 51:11.193
Let's please focus on the trial.

51:18.074 --> 51:19.701
Long time no see, sir.

51:20.368 --> 51:22.287
I'm so glad to see you well.

51:22.370 --> 51:25.081
It's been such a long time.

51:25.165 --> 51:27.209
I was sad that you left Taebaek.

51:27.876 --> 51:30.670
But I'm relieved
to see you work with Attorney Shin.

51:31.671 --> 51:33.757
All right. Let's play fair.

51:33.840 --> 51:34.841
Yes, sir.

51:43.934 --> 51:46.436
Aren't you being too sweet to Shin I-rang?

51:47.145 --> 51:48.146
Am I?

51:49.356 --> 51:50.649
Then again,

51:50.732 --> 51:53.985
you don't know what kind of freak he is.

52:17.384 --> 52:18.385
Oh, my.

52:22.055 --> 52:24.266
Why is this out here?

52:41.199 --> 52:42.200
This can't be.

52:45.203 --> 52:47.914
TO MY DEAR BELOVED H,
FROM DONG-SIK

52:55.380 --> 52:56.715
Hold on.

53:01.803 --> 53:07.976
Let the trial begin
for Case 2025-Gahab-1901458.

53:11.646 --> 53:13.315
Ms. Chae is running late.

53:15.317 --> 53:16.693
I know.

53:17.277 --> 53:18.278
Where's Mr. Kang?

53:18.945 --> 53:19.988
He's in the truck.

53:20.071 --> 53:21.907
He's not going to come. Don't worry.

53:24.200 --> 53:26.786
This trial has been convened
following the lawsuit

53:26.870 --> 53:30.874
filed by Plaintiff Kang Ji-hoon,
claiming that the will of his late father,

53:30.957 --> 53:33.877
Kang Dong-sik, is invalid
while Defendant Chae Jeong-hui,

53:33.960 --> 53:37.547
his mother, maintains
the mandatory execution of the will.

53:38.214 --> 53:41.343
Defense counsel,
you may begin your opening statement.

53:47.557 --> 53:51.478
In 1979, Kang Dong-sik, Chae Jeong-hui,
and Ryeo Seon Hwa opened Ideal Shoes

53:51.561 --> 53:56.316
in the alley for handmade shoes
in Malli-dong and became co-owners.

53:57.067 --> 54:01.237
I've submitted corporate documents
and pictures to prove this.

54:01.321 --> 54:02.739
EXHIBITS 2-1, 2-2, 4-1, 4-3

54:04.324 --> 54:07.661
Ms. Ryeo Seon Hwa's leatherworking skills

54:07.744 --> 54:11.498
served as a foundation
for the growth of their business.

54:11.581 --> 54:15.752
In recognition of her contributions,
the late Chairman Kang Dong-sik

54:15.835 --> 54:20.799
left a will to bequeath one-third
of the inheritance to Ms. Ryeo's son.

54:34.521 --> 54:37.691
Therefore, as the representative
of the defendant,

54:37.774 --> 54:40.443
I demand that Plaintiff Kang Ji-hoon

54:40.527 --> 54:44.572
promptly execute the will
of the late Chairman Kang Dong-sik

54:44.656 --> 54:48.076
and transfer one-third of the inheritance
to Ms. Ryeo's son, Cha Eun Seong.

54:48.159 --> 54:49.244
That is all.

55:04.134 --> 55:07.470
We'd love to carry out the will…

55:09.639 --> 55:12.559
if the chairman's will is genuine.

55:13.685 --> 55:17.063
Ms. Chae Jeong-hui, the wife
of the late Chairman Kang Dong-sik,

55:17.147 --> 55:20.025
has proved it to be
her husband's handwriting.

55:22.235 --> 55:23.236
That's right.

55:24.612 --> 55:26.948
With the help of the Korea Institute
of Document Examination,

55:27.032 --> 55:28.533
a thorough analysis of the will

55:29.117 --> 55:32.912
shows that the will was indeed
written by the chairman.

55:32.996 --> 55:35.498
But the problem lies elsewhere.

55:36.958 --> 55:37.959
Attorney Shin I-rang.

55:39.002 --> 55:41.546
Will you tell me
when the will was written?

55:44.257 --> 55:46.885
What for?
It obviously says so on the will.

55:46.968 --> 55:49.345
Please tell me when it was written.

55:54.684 --> 55:57.854
June 12, 2019.

55:58.772 --> 56:02.150
Correct, and that is the problem.

56:02.233 --> 56:03.485
Why is that a problem?

56:04.319 --> 56:08.031
Chairman Kang Dong-sik's symptoms
of Alzheimer's worsened in 2021.

56:08.615 --> 56:12.744
And the will was written in 2019,
which is 2 years before that.

56:12.827 --> 56:16.331
Was it really written in 2019?

56:21.628 --> 56:23.129
WILL
I, KANG DONG-SIK…

56:24.422 --> 56:26.883
WILL

56:27.467 --> 56:31.304
The analysis result
of the ink used in the will shows

56:31.387 --> 56:34.974
that it was written
with a Napoleon fountain pen.

56:35.058 --> 56:36.810
The company of this fountain pen

56:36.893 --> 56:39.979
raised the pH level of its black ink

56:40.063 --> 56:44.776
from 6.7 to 7.2 to improve its smoothness
in November of 2022.

56:45.527 --> 56:46.736
Surprisingly enough,

56:47.320 --> 56:51.533
the pH level of the ink used in the will,
which was supposedly written in June 2019,

56:51.616 --> 56:53.326
turned out to be 7.2.

56:55.036 --> 56:59.040
Thus, it cannot be established as fact
that the will was written in June 2019.

56:59.874 --> 57:02.210
Besides, in November of 2022,

57:02.293 --> 57:05.171
the chairman could not recognize his wife

57:05.255 --> 57:07.549
as well as his own son
due to severe dementia.

57:08.591 --> 57:11.761
Attached is a expert testimony
from a medical specialist.

57:11.845 --> 57:12.971
Objection!

57:13.054 --> 57:14.055
Let us hear more.

57:15.098 --> 57:16.099
Thank you.

57:16.850 --> 57:17.976
Now,

57:18.059 --> 57:22.605
if the will wasn't written by the chairman
whose disease was worsening at the time,

57:23.440 --> 57:26.484
who could it be that wrote the will?

57:32.740 --> 57:35.285
Through document anti-forgery software,

57:35.368 --> 57:38.037
we examined the similarities
between the will

57:38.121 --> 57:40.123
and the writings
of another particular person.

57:40.206 --> 57:41.207
The result shows

57:41.791 --> 57:45.044
that the usage frequency
of conjunctive words and pronouns

57:45.128 --> 57:48.089
and the placement of verbs
match by more than 94%.

57:49.841 --> 57:51.342
This particular person is…

58:05.648 --> 58:07.275
DAEUN CHOCOLATE

58:22.707 --> 58:23.750
Are you done?

58:23.833 --> 58:25.460
Yes, I'm almost done.

58:28.254 --> 58:30.006
They're beautiful.

58:30.924 --> 58:31.925
Aren't they?

59:17.554 --> 59:19.973
If you were sound of mind,

59:21.182 --> 59:24.060
you would've agreed with me.

59:26.020 --> 59:27.021
Honey.

59:29.190 --> 59:31.359
Please tell me you do.

59:41.327 --> 59:43.913
Now, hold this.

59:45.290 --> 59:46.374
Write.

59:47.292 --> 59:48.626
-Write?
-Yes.

59:52.046 --> 59:53.047
Write what?

59:53.756 --> 59:55.008
"Will."

59:58.595 --> 01:00:00.972
"I, Kang Dong-sik…"

01:00:01.055 --> 01:00:02.640
<i>I, Kang Dong-sik…</i>

01:00:02.724 --> 01:00:03.850
"…leave this…"

01:00:03.933 --> 01:00:07.186
<i>…leave this as my last will.</i>

01:00:08.730 --> 01:00:10.189
What…

01:00:10.273 --> 01:00:11.399
Honey.

01:00:11.482 --> 01:00:13.067
This particular person is…

01:00:14.444 --> 01:00:15.737
Ms. Chae Jeong-hui.

01:00:22.702 --> 01:00:23.870
His claim doesn't make sense.

01:00:23.953 --> 01:00:26.164
She has no reason to fabricate the will.

01:00:26.247 --> 01:00:27.999
Yes, she does.

01:00:29.000 --> 01:00:31.711
The one who reported Ms. Ryeo Seon Hwa
for being a spy…

01:00:32.712 --> 01:00:34.380
-Let go!
-She's not a spy.

01:00:34.464 --> 01:00:36.549
Seon Hwa!

01:00:36.633 --> 01:00:39.469
…was Ms. Chae Jeong-hui.

01:00:41.638 --> 01:00:43.097
It can't be.

01:00:46.643 --> 01:00:48.061
This is ridiculous!

01:00:49.354 --> 01:00:50.355
Honey.

01:00:51.814 --> 01:00:54.359
I submit the document
of the Military Intelligence Agency.

01:00:55.193 --> 01:00:56.527
INFORMANT: CHAE JEONG-HUI

01:00:58.154 --> 01:01:00.990
Honey! Why would you?

01:01:01.949 --> 01:01:07.455
The document clearly states that
Ms. Chae reported Ms. Ryeo Seon Hwa.

01:01:07.538 --> 01:01:09.874
We were not informed
of this evidence in advance.

01:01:09.957 --> 01:01:11.834
Ms. Chae reported Ms. Ryeo,

01:01:11.918 --> 01:01:14.003
but when Ms. Ryeo passed away in jail,

01:01:14.087 --> 01:01:17.715
she attempted to leave an inheritance
to her son, Cha Eun Seong,

01:01:17.799 --> 01:01:19.550
so that she could offset her guilt

01:01:20.760 --> 01:01:22.929
even by fabricating her husband's will.

01:01:27.308 --> 01:01:28.393
Honey!

01:01:35.525 --> 01:01:37.777
Now that the will is proven to be fake,

01:01:37.860 --> 01:01:40.196
the plaintiff has no duties
to share the inheritance

01:01:40.279 --> 01:01:41.572
with Ryeo Seon Hwa's son.

01:01:41.656 --> 01:01:42.824
No, Mr. Kang.

01:01:42.907 --> 01:01:45.201
-Not now, please.
-There's no reason to continue the trial.

01:01:45.785 --> 01:01:47.036
-What…
-Thus, I request…

01:01:47.120 --> 01:01:49.330
-Say what must be said!
-…a prompt conclusion

01:01:49.414 --> 01:01:50.665
of this trial.

01:01:52.875 --> 01:01:54.669
I wrote it!

01:01:59.590 --> 01:02:00.591
What?

01:02:00.675 --> 01:02:03.553
I wrote the will!

01:02:03.636 --> 01:02:04.637
Me!

01:02:04.721 --> 01:02:06.723
Defense counsel, what are you doing?

01:02:07.348 --> 01:02:10.184
Do you want to be ejected
for perjury and contempt of court?

01:02:10.268 --> 01:02:13.771
Hey, Mr. Judge.
Listen to what I have to say!

01:02:13.855 --> 01:02:14.897
I--

01:02:14.981 --> 01:02:16.149
Your Honor!

01:02:16.232 --> 01:02:18.484
Attorney Shin I-rang has
a serious chronic disease.

01:02:19.360 --> 01:02:23.114
I request a recess
due to his current condition.

01:02:23.197 --> 01:02:24.991
A recess, not a conclusion!

01:03:00.276 --> 01:03:03.196
TO MY DEAR BELOVED H,
FROM DONG-SIK

01:03:12.288 --> 01:03:14.207
Why did you report Ms. Ryeo?

01:03:14.290 --> 01:03:15.541
-<i>I'm sorry.</i>
-<i>Honey.</i>

01:03:15.625 --> 01:03:17.752
<i>But he likes someone else.</i>

01:03:17.835 --> 01:03:20.379
<i>I saw you with him at the workshop.</i>

01:03:20.463 --> 01:03:22.173
Seon Hwa!

01:03:22.256 --> 01:03:23.257
<i>Let's give up on this case.</i>

01:03:23.341 --> 01:03:26.594
What happens if Seon Hwa is alive?

01:03:26.677 --> 01:03:28.054
It'll be a complete game-changer.

01:03:28.137 --> 01:03:30.056
Find where Ryeo Seon Hwa
is buried immediately.

01:03:30.139 --> 01:03:31.641
Some people are looking for you.

01:03:31.724 --> 01:03:33.684
-<i>Run away.</i>
-<i>It's Seon Hwa.</i>

01:03:33.768 --> 01:03:35.353
It's her.

01:03:35.436 --> 01:03:39.774
Subtitle translation by: Eunjin Erica Kim
